{{Infobox FBI Ten Most Wanted | name = Bhadreshkumar Chetanbhai Patel | image =FBI_Most_Wanted_Fugitive_poster,_Bhadreshkumar_Chetanbhai_Patel.pdf | image_size = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|5|15}} | birth_place = [[Viramgam]], [[Gujarat]], [[India]] | birth_name = Bhadreshkumar Chetanbhai Patel | nationality = Indian | alias = | charge = Unlawful Flight to Avoid Prosecution - First Degree Murder, Second Degree Murder, First Degree Assault, Second Degree Assault, Dangerous Weapon with Intent to Injure | conviction = | conviction_penalty = | occupation = [[Dunkin' Donuts]] Employee | spouse = Palak Bhadreshkumar Patel | parents = | siblings = | added_date = April 18, 2017 | caught_date = | remove_date = | number = | status = Missing |Status choices: |No status or other status defaults to currently on list }}
'''Bhadreshkumar Chetanbhai Patel''' (born May 15, 1990) is an Indian [[fugitive]] wanted for allegedly killing his wife at a [[Dunkin Donuts]] in [[Hanover, Maryland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.indiatimes.com/news/india/two-years-on-the-run-for-the-murder-of-his-wife-fbi-puts-indian-man-on-it-s-top-10-most-wanted-list-275963.html |title=Two Years On The Run For The Murder Of His Wife, FBI Puts Indian Man On It's Top 10 ‘Most Wanted List’ |newspaper=[[India Times]] |date=19 April 2017 |access-date=19 August 2018 |publisher=[[Times Internet Limited]] |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20180617121046/https://www.indiatimes.com/news/india/two-years-on-the-run-for-the-murder-of-his-wife-fbi-puts-indian-man-on-it-s-top-10-most-wanted-list-275963.html |archive-date=17 June 2018}}</ref> He was the 514th person to be added to the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]'s list of [[Ten Most Wanted Fugitives]] and was last seen at a local train station near his hotel in [[New Jersey]].
==Background== Patel has connections in [[Canada]], [[India]], New Jersey, [[Kentucky]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] and [[Illinois]]. A reward of up to $100,000 is available for information that leads to his whereabouts.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/public-safety/latest-on-fbis-most-wanted-list-man-accused-of-killing-wife-in-md-doughnut-shop/2017/04/18/ae0a9816-2445-11e7-b503-9d616bd5a305_story.html |title=Latest on FBI's most wanted list: Man accused of killing wife in Md. doughnut shop |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |last=Bui |first=Lynh |date=18 April 2017 |access-date=19 August 2018}}</ref>
