__NOTOC__ {{Infobox ethnic group |group = Laotians in France |image = |pop = 90,000 (2013)<ref name="Présentation du Laos">{{citation|url=http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/pays-zones-geo/laos/presentation-du-laos/|title=Présentation du Laos|publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs|location=France|year=2013|accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref> |popplace = [[Paris]],<ref>{{harvnb|Bouvier|Smith|2006|p=47}}</ref> [[DOM-TOM]], [[French Guiana]]<ref>{{harvnb|Bouvier|Smith|2006|p=47}}</ref> |rels=[[Theravada Buddhism]]<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.buddhanet.info/wbd/search.php?keyword=laotian&prev_keyword%5B%5D=lao&newsearch=new&search=Begin+Search&country_id=62&province_id=0|periodical=World Buddhist Directory|publisher=Buddha Dharma Education Association|title=Lao Buddhist organisations in France|year=2006|accessdate=2010-11-11}}</ref> |langs= [[French language|French]] <small>(standard and [[Lao French|Lao variant]])</small>, [[Lao language|Lao]] |related = [[Laotian diaspora]], [[Asian French|Asians in France]] }}
'''Laotians in France''' consist of people of [[Lao people|Lao]] ancestry who were born in or immigrated to [[France]]. The population as of 2013 is estimated to be 90,000.<ref name="Présentation du Laos"/>
The Laotian community in France forms the most established [[Laotian diaspora|overseas Laotian]] population, with a presence in the country dating to before the end of the [[Laotian Civil War]] and mass refugee migration that resulted from it.<ref>Carine Hahn, ''Le Laos'', Karthala, 1999, page 77</ref>
==History== The presence of Laotian people in France began during the early 20th century, when Laos was a [[French Laos|protectorate of France]]. With the steady introduction of the French education system by the colonists, a number of Laotian students were able to study in France, including members of the [[Lao Royal Family]].<ref>{{harvnb|Hahn|1999|p=77}}</ref> A smaller number of Laotian workers also settled in France during this period. However, the largest influx of Laotians immigrated to France following the [[Vietnam War]] and communist takeover of their homeland.
France was an ideal destination for Laotian refugees who were educated or formed part of the elite and middle class in the home nation, while poorer refugees tended to emigrate to North America and Australia through the assistance of the American, Canadian and Australian governments.<ref>[http://www.immigrantinfo.org/kin/laos.htm Knowledge of Immigrant Nationalities of Santa Clara County (KIN) - Laos<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209045428/http://www.immigrantinfo.org/kin/laos.htm |date=2013-12-09 }}</ref>
==Culture and demographics== Unlike their counterpart communities in the [[Laotian American|United States]], [[Canadians of Laotian descent|Canada]] and [[Laotian Australian|Australia]], Laotians in France are more successful and better integrated into the host country due to stronger knowledge of the nation's social aspects, such as culture, language and history.<ref name="Lao Voices">{{citation|url=http://laovoices.com/life-in-a-foreign-city-can-be-difficult-but-lao-culture-still-prevails/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130315050941/http://laovoices.com/life-in-a-foreign-city-can-be-difficult-but-lao-culture-still-prevails/|title=Life in a foreign city can be difficult but Lao culture still prevails|work=Lao Voices|date=7 January 2012|accessdate=2013-06-22|archivedate=2013-03-15}}</ref> Although the issue of immigrant groups and their level of assimilation has been an important issue in French politics, the Laotian community is highly integrated into French society, with high average rates of educational and economic achievement, especially among the generations of French-born Lao.<ref>[http://sayasackp.free.fr/connaitrejeunesse.htm La jeunesse lao de France, quelle identité?] (in French)</ref>
Laotian Buddhist temples serve as community and cultural centers for the Laotian population in France, and important traditional holidays such as [[Lao New Year]] and the [[Pha That Luang Festival]] are observed in addition to French holidays.<ref>[http://www.lindependant.fr/2012/04/10/nouvel-an-lao-bonne-annee-2555,130094.php Nouvel an Lao] (in French)</ref>
The majority of Laotians in France live in [[Paris]] and the surrounding [[Île-de-France]] region, with smaller communities in [[Marseille]], [[Lille]] and [[Strasbourg]]. While the generation of immigrants to France tries to preserve Laotian culture and uses the Lao language among the community, the first and second generations born in France are increasingly influenced by French culture, with many members of the generations being unable to understand or speak Lao.<ref name="Lao Voices" />
