The '''Logir''' are an ethnic group numbering a few thousand people living in [[Eastern Equatoria]] state, [[South Sudan]].They are part of the Eastern Nilotes who were originally staying in the present land Ethiopia, precisely on an area on top of Lake Turkana. They then moved to South Sudan after being displaced by the Oromia of Ethiopia. They came to Stay at their present place on top of Uganda where they found the Madi people.<ref>{{cite web |title=Logir |url=http://www.gurtong.net/Peoples/PeoplesProfiles/Logir/tabid/206/Default.aspx |publisher=Gurtong |accessdate=June 18, 2014}}</ref>

